== Biscuit Base ==

Keep the oven at 200°C. Chop the @Unsalted Butter{30%g} into ½cm pieces and pop into a #mixing bowl{} with the @Plain Flour{50%g} and @Caster Sugar{30%g}. Use your fingers to rub the mixture until there are no big lumps of butter left and the whole thing has the texture of coarse breadcrumbs. Spread the crumb mixture out on a #baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the mixture is golden, ~{12-18%minutes}. Leave to the side to cool.

Lower your oven temperature to 180°C.

== Ganache ==

Break the @Chocolate{100%g} up into small chunks and zest the @Orange{1}. Pop both in a #bowl{} together. Pour the @Double Cream{150%ml}(for the ganache) into a #small saucepan{} and bring to the boil over medium heat. Once the cream boils, remove from the heat and immediately pour into the bowl of chocolate and orange. Stir until you have a smooth and glossy chocolate mixture - this is your ganache!

== Assembly ==

Pour the @Double Cream{250%ml}(for whipping) into a #large bowl{} and whisk by hand until the cream has slightly thickened to the consistency of a thick yoghurt.

> TIP: You can use an electric whisk but be careful not to make it too thick as this will make your chocolate pot very dense!

Slowly pour the ganache into the thickened cream and gently fold the mixture together with a #large spoon{}. Don't over mix, you don't want to knock all the air out of it. If the cream and ganache aren't completely combined, don't worry, you want it slightly marbled!

Gently break up the crumb mixture using the back of a #metal spoon{} or a #rolling pin{} and divide between the bottom of some small glasses (use your nicest glasses for ultimate presentation points). Spoon the chocolate mixture on top, cover with #clingfilm{} and pop into your fridge (ready for the next day).

== Caramelised Nuts ==

Shell the @Pistachios{25%g}. Spread your pistachios and @Pecan Nuts{40%g} out on a baking tray lined with #non stick baking paper{}. Drizzle over the @Honey{2%tbsp} and mix to thoroughly coat your nuts. Spread them out in an even layer and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and sticky ~{7-10%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch like a hawk to ensure they don't burn!

When cooked, leave to one side to cool completely then roughly chop and store in an #airtight container{} at room temperature.

> TIP: Don't be tempted to refrigerate your nuts or they will go soggy!